# Search against the Planetary Computer STAC API
catalog = Client.open(
  "https://planetarycomputer.microsoft.com/api/stac/v1"
)

# Define your area of interest
aoi = {
  "type": "Polygon",
  "coordinates": [
    [
      [6.190670576165132, 45.143295424405636],
      [7.153704675046896, 45.143295424405636],
      [7.153704675046896, 45.55137984313984],
      [6.190670576165132, 45.55137984313984],
      [6.190670576165132, 45.143295424405636]
    ]
  ]
}

# select date ranges
dateranges = [
    {"interval": ["1994-01-01T00:00:00Z", "1996-12-31T23:59:59Z"]},
    {"interval": ["2008-01-01T00:00:00Z", "2010-12-31T23:59:59Z"]},
    {"interval": ["2021-01-01T00:00:00Z", "2023-12-31T23:59:59Z"]}
]

# loop through date ranges, load, and save backup of data
## creates a variable per period
for daterange in range(len(dateranges)):
    # Define your search with CQL2 syntax
    search = catalog.search(filter_lang="cql2-json", filter={
    "op": "and",
    "args": [
        {"op": "s_intersects", "args": [{"property": "geometry"}, aoi]},
        {"op": "anyinteracts", "args": [{"property": "datetime"}, \
            dateranges[daterange]]},
        {"op": "=", "args": [{"property": "collection"}, "landsat-c2-l2"]},
        {"op": "<=", "args": [{"property": "eo:cloud_cover"}, 20]}
    ]
    })

    # Retrieve items
    sat = search.get_all_items()
    print("Number of images from search:", len(sat)) 

    # Stack the images on top of eachother
    ds_sat = stackstac.stack(pc.sign(sat), epsg=32632)

    # Set a small area around Les Trois Vallees ski resort
    xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax = 300077, 319481, 5007954, 5037053
    ltv = ds_sat.loc[:,:, ymax:ymin,xmin:xmax]

    ## get quality assessment band
    cloud_qa = ltv.sel(band="cloud_qa")
    ## get necessary bands
    green = ltv.sel(band='green')
    swir1 = ltv.sel(band='swir16')

    # calculate NDSI
    ndsi = (green-swir1) / (green+swir1)

    # mask clouds (2: clouds, 3: cirrus)
    ndsi_cm = xr.where((~cloud_qa.isin([2, 3])), ndsi, np.nan)

    # resample timeseries per month
    #ndsi_ms = ndsi.resample(time="MS").mean(dim="time", skipna=True)
    ndsi_ms_cm = ndsi_cm.resample(time="MS").mean(dim="time", skipna=True)

    with dask.diagnostics.ProgressBar():
        globals()[f"ts_{daterange}"] = ndsi_ms_cm.compute()

    varname = str(globals()[f"ts_{daterange}"].time[0].values)[:4]
    filename = f'out/ts_ndsi_cm_3y_{varname}_{varname}.nc'
    globals()[f"ts_{daterange}"].to_netcdf(filename)

# add scale bar to all axes
def add_scale(fig, plots=-1):
    for ax in fig.get_axes()[:plots]:
        ax.add_artist(ScaleBar(1, location="lower right"))

# add arrow to all axes
def add_northarrow(fig, plots=-1, x=0.9, y=0.15, arrow_length=0.05):
    for ax in fig.get_axes()[:plots]:
        ax.annotate('N', xy=(x, y), xytext=(x, y-arrow_length),
                arrowprops=dict(facecolor='black', width=5, headwidth=15),
                ha='center', va='center', fontsize=20,
                xycoords=ax.transAxes)

# count months of snow per year in period
snow_y_0 = ts_0_ip.resample(time="YS").sum(dim="time", skipna=True)
snow_y_1 = ts_1_ip.resample(time="YS").sum(dim="time", skipna=True)
snow_y_2 = ts_2_ip.resample(time="YS").sum(dim="time", skipna=True)

# average pixel NDSI per month within period 
snow_p_0 = ts_0_ip.groupby("time.month").mean(dim='time', skipna=True)
snow_p_1 = ts_1_ip.groupby("time.month").mean(dim='time', skipna=True)
snow_p_2 = ts_2_ip.groupby("time.month").mean(dim='time', skipna=True)

# Apply >= 0.4 on averaged data as questioned above
### there are locations which almost impossibly cannot have snow due to the high slope !!!
snow_p_0_h = xr.where(snow_p_0.notnull(), snow_p_0 > 0.4, np.nan)
snow_p_1_h = xr.where(snow_p_1.notnull(), snow_p_1 > 0.4, np.nan)
snow_p_2_h = xr.where(snow_p_2.notnull(), snow_p_2 > 0.4, np.nan)

# averaged periodical snow duration
snow_3y_0 = snow_p_0_h.sum(dim="month", skipna=False)
snow_3y_1 = snow_p_1_h.sum(dim="month", skipna=False)
snow_3y_2 = snow_p_2_h.sum(dim="month", skipna=False)

# define north and south facing masks
north_facing_range1 = (0, 90)           # only northwards quarter (0|315, 45|360)
north_facing_range2 = (270, 360)
south_facing_range = (90, 270)          # only southwards quarter (135, 225)  

north_mask1 = xr.where(
    (aspect >= north_facing_range1[0]) & (aspect <= north_facing_range1[1]),
    True, False)
north_mask2 = xr.where(
    (aspect > north_facing_range2[0]) & (aspect <= north_facing_range2[1]),
    True, False)
north_mask = (north_mask1 + north_mask2)
south_mask = xr.where(
    (aspect > south_facing_range[0]) & (aspect <= south_facing_range[1]),
    True, False)

# plot masks
fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3) = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=3, figsize=(15, 5))

ax1.set_title('North Facing Aspects')
south_mask.plot(ax=ax2)
ax2.set_title('South Facing Aspects')

ax3.set_title('north_mask + south_mask')

h_count_tot = higher_mask.sum()

h_count_1 = snow_p_0_h.where(higher_mask).sum(dim=("x", "y")) / h_count_tot * 100
h_count_2 = snow_p_1_h.where(higher_mask).sum(dim=("x", "y")) / h_count_tot * 100
h_count_3 = snow_p_2_h.where(higher_mask).sum(dim=("x", "y")) / h_count_tot * 100

df_h_percent = pd.DataFrame(
    {"h1994-1996": h_count_1,
    "h2008-2010": h_count_2,
    "h2021-2023": h_count_3})

df_lh_percent = pd.concat([df_h_percent, df_l_percent], axis=1)
df_lh_percent.to_csv("out_data/lowhighelevation_comparison.csv")
